al for the formulation of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Quantum_mechanics\" title=\"Quantum mechanics\">quantum mechanics<\/a>. Wien received the 1911 Nobel Prize for his work on <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Heat_radiation\" title=\"Heat radiation\" class=\"mw-redirect\">heat radiation<\/a>.<\/p>","name":"Wilhelm Wien","place_of_birth":"Fischhausen ,  East Prussia","place_of_death":"Munich ,  Germany","text":"Wilhelm Wien , Physics, 1911","year":1911.0}